  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  The evidences of hepatitis B virus (HBV)&amp;/or hepatitis C virus (HCV) infection or
             liver cirrhosis

          -  Single tumor nodule with Child-Pugh classification A (serum albumin â‰¥ 3.2 g/dL)

          -  The maximal, longest diameter of tumor mass measured by CT finding should be less than
             2 cm

          -  Only for the newly detected HCCs which were not treated before

          -  It should be compatible with the typical finding of hepatocellular carcinomas (HCCs)
             radiologically (MD CT or dynamic MRI)

          -  Without portal hypertension

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  In case of hepatic vein or portal vein invasion radiologically (CT or MRI)
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
